    "description": "Join the Practo Advisory Limited family as a Full Stack Developer in Jabalpur. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout Practo Advisory Limited:\nPracto Advisory Limited is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Write and execute unit tests and integration tests\n• Work with agile methodologies including daily stand-ups and sprint planning\n• Ensure code security and follow best practices for data protection\n• Contribute to system architecture and technical design decisions\n• Mentor junior developers and conduct knowledge-sharing sessions\n• Write clean, maintainable, and well-documented code\n• Collaborate with cross-functional teams including product, design, and QA\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBA from a recognized university\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Docker\n• Proficiency in Agile/Scrum\n• Proficiency in CI/CD\n• Proficiency in Kubernetes\n• Proficiency in JavaScript\n• Proficiency in Python\n• Proficiency in Go\n• Proficiency in Microservices\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Practo Advisory Limited!",
